### 6.3 Implement Focus Trap in Modals

**Existing modals:**
- POS selection modal (`#posSelectionModal`)
- Payment modal (`#paymentModal`)
- Delete confirmation overlay (dynamic)
- Dish/rider modals (`#dishModal`, `#riderModal`)

**Create reusable `trapFocus(modalElement)` function:**

```javascript
function trapFocus(modal) {
  const focusable = modal.querySelectorAll(
    'button, [href], input, select, textarea, [tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"])'
  );
  const first = focusable[0];
  const last = focusable[focusable.length - 1];
  
  first.focus();
  
  modal.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
    if (e.key === 'Tab') {
      if (e.shiftKey) {
        if (document.activeElement === first) {
          e.preventDefault();
          last.focus();
        }
      } else {
        if (document.activeElement === last) {
          e.preventDefault();
          first.focus();
        }
      }
    }
    if (e.key === 'Escape') {
      modal.style.display = 'none';
    }
  });
}

// Usage in showPOSSelectionModal():
document.getElementById('posSelectionModal').style.display = 'flex';
trapFocus(document.getElementById('posSelectionModal'));
```

